## API Design

### Response envelope

Every response ŌĆö success or failure ŌĆö must use this shape. No exceptions. Consistent shape means every client can write one response handler.

```ts
type ApiResponse<T> = {
  data: T | null;
  error: { code: string; message: string; details?: unknown } | null;
  meta?: { page: number; limit: number; total: number };
};

// Ō£ģ Success
{ data: { id: '123', name: 'Alice' }, error: null }

// Ō£ģ Error
{ data: null, error: { code: 'USER_NOT_FOUND', message: 'User not found: id=123' } }

// Ō£ģ Paginated list
{ data: [...], error: null, meta: { page: 1, limit: 20, total: 340 } }
```

### URL conventions

- All routes prefixed: `/api/v1/`
- Nouns, not verbs: `/api/v1/users`, not `/api/v1/getUsers`
- Nested resources for ownership: `/api/v1/users/:userId/orders`
- Never change a versioned API ŌĆö create `/api/v2/` instead

### HTTP status codes

Use these consistently ŌĆö never return `200` for an error:

| Scenario                    | Code |
| --------------------------- | ---- |
| Successful GET / PUT        | 200  |
| Successful POST (created)   | 201  |
| Successful DELETE (no body) | 204  |
| Validation error            | 422  |
| Unauthenticated             | 401  |
| Unauthorized (wrong role)   | 403  |
| Not found                   | 404  |
| Internal error              | 500  |

### Pagination

All list endpoints must be paginated. Use cursor-based pagination for large datasets (avoids OFFSET scanning):

```ts
// Query params: GET /api/v1/orders?limit=20&cursor=<lastId>
// Response meta always includes total count and next cursor
meta: { limit: 20, total: 1540, nextCursor: 'eyJpZCI6IjEwMCJ9' }
```

Default `limit=20`, maximum `limit=100`. Reject requests above the max with a 422.

