## Testing

Think of tests like a safety net under a trapeze ŌĆö unit tests catch individual missteps, integration tests catch handoff errors.

### File conventions

- Unit tests: `*.test.ts` ŌĆö lives next to the file it tests (`user.service.test.ts`)
- Integration tests: `*.spec.ts` ŌĆö lives in `/tests/` at the project root
- Test naming: `describe('UserService')` ŌåÆ `it('should throw NotFoundError when user does not exist')`

### What to test

| Layer           | Test type   | What to cover                                         |
| --------------- | ----------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Services        | Unit        | Every function, happy path + all error branches       |
| Repositories    | Unit        | Mock DB, test query logic                             |
| Routes          | Integration | Every endpoint ŌĆö happy path + min. 2 error cases      |
| Auth middleware | Unit        | Valid token, expired token, missing token, wrong role |
| Event consumers | Unit        | Happy path + duplicate event (idempotency)            |

### What NOT to test

- Implementation details or private methods
- Framework internals (Express routing, Zod parsing internals)
- Tests that just assert `true === true` ŌĆö coverage for its own sake is noise

### Coverage

Enforce a minimum of **80% line coverage** in CI. A test that exists but doesn't assert anything meaningful is worse than no test.

```ts
// Arrange ŌåÆ Act ŌåÆ Assert ŌĆö always this order
it('should throw NotFoundError when user does not exist', async () => {
  // Arrange
  mockUserRepo.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);

  // Act & Assert
  await expect(userService.getById('missing-id')).rejects.toThrow(
    NotFoundError
  );
});
```

