## Performance

- Avoid N+1 queries ŌĆö batch or eager-load related data
- Use `Promise.all()` for concurrent independent async tasks
- Cache expensive or repeated operations (Redis for shared cache, LRU for in-process)
- Stream large payloads instead of buffering entirely in memory
- Set timeouts on all outbound HTTP/DB calls ŌĆö never leave them open-ended
- Use `OFFSET` pagination only for small datasets ŌĆö use cursor-based for anything large

---

## Security

- Validate + sanitize all input at the API boundary with Zod
- Use parameterized queries ŌĆö **no SQL string interpolation, ever**
- Hash passwords with `bcrypt` (cost Ōēź 12) or `argon2` ŌĆö never plain or MD5
- Short-lived JWTs + refresh token rotation (see Auth section)
- Apply principle of least privilege to IAM roles and DB users
- Run `npm audit` in CI ŌĆö fail the build on high-severity vulnerabilities
- Never log sensitive data: no passwords, tokens, card numbers, or PII in logs

