## CI/CD & Deployment

### Required pipeline stages (in order)

1. `lint` ŌĆö ESLint + Prettier check (fail fast, no style debates in PRs)
2. `type-check` ŌĆö `tsc --noEmit` catches type errors without building
3. `test` ŌĆö unit + integration tests with coverage threshold enforced
4. `build` ŌĆö production build (catches missing env vars, bad imports)
5. `deploy` ŌĆö only on `main` branch, only after all above pass

### Required endpoints

Every service must expose:

- `GET /health` ŌĆö returns `{ status: 'ok', uptime: N, version: string }` ŌĆö used by load balancers and monitoring
- `GET /ready` ŌĆö returns `{ status: 'ok' }` only when DB + Redis connections are established

### Lambda-specific rules

- No shared mutable state outside the handler function ŌĆö Lambda instances are reused unpredictably
- Initialize DB/Redis connections outside the handler but handle reconnection inside
- Always set function timeout lower than the SQS visibility timeout to avoid duplicate processing
- Keep cold start time low: avoid heavy imports at the top level, use lazy initialization

### Secrets & config

- Secrets always via environment variables ŌĆö never in code, never baked into Docker images
- Use AWS Secrets Manager or SSM Parameter Store in production ŌĆö never plain `.env` files in deployed environments
- `.env.example` must be kept up to date and committed ŌĆö `.env` is always in `.gitignore`

